As you've done the R rated versions of Marvel movies, I would love to see a "real version" of Star Wars. Like, super anti-climatic moments with no sound of explosions at all in space or an asteroid belt with asteroids completely distant from each other (no real threat to any small ship at all).
I know, it doesn't sound awesome, but it's good to show the magic of cinema. Sometimes, you have to throw real physics through the window in order to get a better movie.

snippet.textDisplay: During the snowspeeder cockpit scenes on Hoth, you can see the canopy pillars are actually sliiiiiightly transparent (you can see the AT-AT's legs through the pillar). Apparently this was due to a limitation with the chroma-keying tech available at the time, which would cause noticeable "outlines" around the mattes, due to the bright white snow background. (In the space battle scenes in A New Hope, the black space didn't cause outlines.) The only way to avoid it was to double expose the shot like they talked about, so you get the background AT-AT legs showing up through the foreground canopy pillars.
snippet.textOriginal: During the snowspeeder cockpit scenes on Hoth, you can see the canopy pillars are actually sliiiiiightly transparent (you can see the AT-AT's legs through the pillar). The only way to avoid it was to double expose the shot like they talked about, so you get the background AT-AT legs showing up through the foreground canopy pillars.

snippet.textDisplay: Fellas.  You should take a look are Adywan's Star Wars: Revisited.  It's the only version of the original trilogy most of will watch now.  After Lucas screwed the pooch with his Special editions and refused to acknowledge the existence on the ORIGINAL films Adywan fixed all the mistakes Lucas did with color, unnecessary added scenes and audio.  Ady has done A New Hope and Empire and is currently in the middle of Jedi.  They are available for FREE download.  He makes NO money from this.  He just wanted to bring back the original glory to these movies that Lucasfilm has forgotten.  He enhanced the Hoth battle with his little home computer so much that it makes people wonder what the hell the people at Lucasfilm are even doing in the first place to earn a paycheck.
